\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering testing strategies**\\n\\nI need a public top-level method and possibly want to use JUnit with AssertJ. I’m thinking about implementing an identity or case strategy, as well. It might be useful to copy the integer variant and focus on a dedicated dynamic-access class specifically for one-to-one mapping. I’ll also need to add a file for reference, and perhaps the report mentions that the active class should be used exclusively. I should get started on writing that!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_7j7FsKmmjhQQo3gB1dkS3nxO|fc_080b8a2db2a2e42b0169fb24b4e7a881968ede28d7d2c6a678", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.sf.trove4j/core/3.1.0/src/test/java/net_sf_trove4j/core/TObjectIntCustomHashMapTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage net_sf_trove4j.core;\n\nimport gnu.trove.map.custom_hash.TObjectIntCustomHashMap;\nimport gnu.trove.strategy.HashingStrategy;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class TObjectIntCustomHashMapTest {\n    @Test\n    void keysAllocatesTypedArrayWhenProvidedArrayIsTooSmall() {\n        TObjectIntCustomHashMap<String> map = new TObjectIntCustomHashMap<>(new CaseInsensitiveHashingStrategy());\n\n        map.put(\"Alpha\", 1);\n        map.put(\"Beta\", 2);\n\n        String[] keys = map.keys(new String[0]);\n\n        assertThat(keys).isInstanceOf(String[].class);\n        assertThat(keys).containsExactlyInAnyOrder(\"Alpha\", \"Beta\");\n        assertThat(map.get(\"alpha\")).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(map.get(\"BETA\")).isEqualTo(2);\n    }\n\n    private static final class CaseInsensitiveHashingStrategy implements HashingStrategy<String> {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n        @Override\n        public int computeHashCode(String object) {\n            return object.toLowerCase().hashCode();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public boolean equals(String first, String second) {\n            return first.equalsIgnoreCase(second);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 536, "output": 483, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28667, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778066607541, "responseId": "resp_080b8a2db2a2e42b0169fb24b032108196b29cfdb0beef7958"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_7j7FsKmmjhQQo3gB1dkS3nxO|fc_080b8a2db2a2e42b0169fb24b4e7a881968ede28d7d2c6a678", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1440 bytes to tests/src/net.sf.trove4j/core/3.1.0/src/test/java/net_sf_trove4j/core/TObjectIntCustomHashMapTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778066614172}]}
